N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1ยง 8.6 - Illegal use of identification stamp or stencil

State Regulations

Whenever the commissioner has evidence that any
identification stamp or stencil has been used contrary to law or to the
provisions of this Part, he may direct the person to whom such stamp or stencil
was issued to return such stamp or stencil to the commissioner and may order
the obliteration or removal of any identification markings which were
wrongfully made. Notes
